Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.03,0:00:04.50,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As times change,\Ndifficult cases increase in number!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.50,0:00:06.73,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A super-creepy bandaged man!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.73,0:00:08.83,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I won't let him go after Ran anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.83,0:00:10.77,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.77,0:00:13.14,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.14,0:00:15.44,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.22,0:01:40.39,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ayako Suzuki (24)\NPresently, Graduate Student
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.18,0:01:44.85,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Masaru Ota (24)\NPresently, Import Car Broker
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.06,0:01:47.94,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hiroki Sumiya (25)\NPresently, Film Magazine Editor
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.31,0:01:51.15,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ryoichi Takahashi (25)\NPresently, Food Company Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.23,0:01:55.03,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Chikako Ikeda (24)\NPresently, Scriptwriter
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.11,0:01:34.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran and I met Sonoko Suzuki\Nat her mountain villa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.68,0:01:37.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}to view the autumn leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.01,0:01:40.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Also there was Sonoko's sister and graduate student, Ayako,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.39,0:01:44.85,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ayako's old college friend and import car broker, Masaru Ota,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.85,0:01:47.94,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the film magazine editor, Hiroki Sumiya,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.94,0:01:51.15,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the food company employee, Ryoichi Takahashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.15,0:01:55.03,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and scriptwriter Chikako Ikeda, for a total of eight people.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.03,0:01:59.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The incidents began when a creepy man in bandages
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.01,0:02:01.57,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}tried to kill Ran in the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.04,0:02:07.52,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That night, after the only bridge out was destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.52,0:02:11.55,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ikeda Chikako was caught and killed by the bandaged man!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.55,0:02:16.25,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And then he tried to kill Ran again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.46,0:02:25.42,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why? Why is he after Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.24,0:02:38.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.01,0:02:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was attacked again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.65,0:02:41.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By that bandaged man?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.68,0:02:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently so...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.48,0:02:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.47,0:02:45.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.49,0:02:47.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did he get in?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.36,0:02:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did lock the window, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.11,0:02:49.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.62,0:02:50.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.22,0:02:50.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.79,0:02:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The window's been cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.45,0:02:53.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aha!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.43,0:02:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He put his hand through to unlock it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.83,0:02:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we're on the second floor! How'd he get up here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.97,0:03:01.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ota! There!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.97,0:03:04.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must've used that tree to climb onto the balcony!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.91,0:03:06.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is one serious guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.76,0:03:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then he—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.71,0:03:11.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's odd—it's pouring outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.05,0:03:13.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If he snuck in from out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.21,0:03:15.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}it's safe to assume he would track mud inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.35,0:03:17.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But there isn't any at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.59,0:03:20.14,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.79,0:03:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's dangerous to be alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.99,0:03:26.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's all wait in the dining room until morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.39,0:03:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good call...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.86,0:03:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hate piggyback rides! They're so stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.87,0:03:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? You sprained your ankle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.67,0:03:37.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Isn't that the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.91,0:03:40.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was wearing around her neck?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.68,0:03:43.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is Chikako's choker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.51,0:03:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right after you and the others chased after the bandaged man,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.68,0:03:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it lying by the front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.49,0:03:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell is the guy thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.09,0:04:02.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Killing Chikako and attacking Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} twice!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:04.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if he wants to kill us all?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.97,0:04:06.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.22,0:04:07.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.10,0:04:10.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.71,0:04:15.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He carried Chikako{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} into the forest afterward,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.31,0:04:18.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}so if her choker did fall off,\Nit would've been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.38,0:04:21.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So what was it doing by the front door?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.22,0:04:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you use your karate to beat him up when he attacked you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.12,0:04:27.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not like you, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.72,0:04:31.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't help it; I'm scared of monsters and stuff like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.80,0:04:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.13,0:04:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's six of us, and one of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.40,0:04:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I doubt he's dumb enough to attack six—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.61,0:04:45.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.94,0:04:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Ow!\N- Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.08,0:04:48.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.95,0:04:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell was that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.85,0:04:53.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's seven people here, not six!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.35,0:04:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're just a kid; you don't count!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.18,0:04:59.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.22,0:05:02.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He protected me when I was attacked!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.49,0:05:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.89,0:05:07.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.50,0:05:12.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Ran. Did you get a look at the guy's face?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.60,0:05:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.30,0:05:16.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know his build, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:18.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't see his face since it was wrapped in bandages,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.87,0:05:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I know his figure because of when I jumped onto him...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.28,0:05:29.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His chest was about this big,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.22,0:05:33.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he wasn't especially skinny or fat...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.65,0:05:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like we can believe what some kid says.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.90,0:05:44.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sumiya{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s video camera!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.23,0:05:47.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm pretty sure he was recording when the bandaged man
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.17,0:05:49.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}ran off with Chikako{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.27,0:05:54.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.24,0:05:58.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just as I thought, she has the choker on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.51,0:06:01.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which means that her body, which the bandaged man
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.42,0:06:04.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}was holding when they passed by the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.95,0:06:09.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}somehow went through this lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.09,0:06:12.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Someone inside this lodge could have carried her
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.19,0:06:15.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}through the house and out into the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.70,0:06:20.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But everyone was in this room\Nwhen she was taken!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.31,0:06:28.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall I make us some coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.04,0:06:29.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.28,0:06:34.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say. You were the last one to see Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.85,0:06:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.58,0:06:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did she seem out of the ordinary at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.45,0:06:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.59,0:06:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she read a note that had been slipped beneath her door...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.46,0:06:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She suddenly turned very pale...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.93,0:06:54.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ah, so she was drawn outside by that note!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.67,0:06:57.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's why her slippers were by the back door—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.17,0:06:59.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}that's where she snuck out from...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.54,0:07:04.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And only someone on the inside could have put the note there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.68,0:07:08.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Does that mean the killer is in this room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.95,0:07:13.69,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But why did he try to kill Ran twice?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.69,0:07:17.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I don't know his motive for killing Chikako{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.02,0:07:21.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but why Ran, who came here at a moment's notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.96,0:07:24.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait a minute! What if she had—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.70,0:07:29.64,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm sorry! My mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.17,0:07:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.84,0:07:32.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.27,0:07:34.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we got here,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.11,0:07:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you opened everyone's door by accident, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.78,0:07:37.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.61,0:07:39.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.18,0:07:40.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.60,0:07:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like a cape or bandages?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.42,0:07:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me this kid suspects us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.32,0:07:49.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't pay attention to him;\Nhe just loves playing detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.52,0:07:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really didn't see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.55,0:07:53.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't see anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were all changing clothes so I shut the doors right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.60,0:07:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:03.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,something's been bugging me ever since...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.34,0:08:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think it was important,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.47,0:08:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I can't remember what it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.28,0:08:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try to remember, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.78,0:08:13.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The power's out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:16.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lightning knocked out a power line!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.48,0:08:18.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.01,0:08:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll get candles from the kitchen!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.69,0:08:22.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You gonna be alright by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.69,0:08:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll come with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.95,0:08:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.56,0:08:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This should help for a little while...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.23,0:08:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.64,0:08:36.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It came from the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.70,0:08:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be the bandaged man again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.11,0:08:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.32,0:08:49.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was mean, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.85,0:08:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.99,0:08:52.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.62,0:08:56.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that an axe?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.82,0:08:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that person just now was—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.13,0:09:03.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The bandaged man{\i0} is {\i1}after Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.00,0:09:04.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But why her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.47,0:09:09.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sounded like Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.24,0:09:11.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.10,0:09:12.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.41,0:09:16.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The upstairs window is broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.94,0:09:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}! Go up to the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.95,0:09:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Could you hold these?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.68,0:09:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this mess!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.55,0:09:28.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The floor's covered in broken glass!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.06,0:09:32.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bandaged man must've broken through this window...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.69,0:09:34.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, he didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.73,0:09:37.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}One of the locks is undone!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.47,0:09:45.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If he really did break in through this window...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.57,0:09:49.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...then it should still be locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.38,0:09:51.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But it's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.58,0:09:54.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Most likely, he unlocked it from the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.45,0:09:56.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}stepped onto the balcony, closed the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.78,0:10:01.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and then smashed it to make it look like he broke in from outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.92,0:10:05.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He snuck in from the 2nd floor again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.09,0:10:09.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he probably jumped onto the balcony from that tree...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.33,0:10:10.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.76,0:10:12.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The maniac who killed Chikako{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.43,0:10:15.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and attacked Ran three times is in this very room!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.37,0:10:22.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What are those grooves?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.34,0:10:24.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it! Now I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.95,0:10:27.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That was a trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.85,0:10:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.15,0:10:36.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But why is the bandaged man intent on killing Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.76,0:10:40.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What exactly did she see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.26,0:10:41.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I didn't see anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.93,0:10:45.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They were all changing clothes so I shut the doors right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.43,0:10:47.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What if he's actually—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.84,0:10:51.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So the bandaged man really is him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.64,0:10:52.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If so, then the three mysteries—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.91,0:10:56.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the reason why the bandaged man passed by the window
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.01,0:10:58.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}with Chikako{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} for everyone to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.78,0:11:02.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}how he was able to carry the body into the forest unnoticed,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.22,0:11:04.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and the reason he's after Ran-
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.45,0:11:06.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}they all fit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.29,0:11:07.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.52,0:11:10.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran's the only detective I can use here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.26,0:11:13.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, where are the candles I gave you earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.80,0:11:16.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I missed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.70,0:11:23.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.50,0:11:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Sonoko?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.17,0:11:29.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn! I have no choice but to use Sonoko now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.01,0:11:30.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.34,0:11:34.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just figured it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.22,0:11:37.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know who killed Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.16,0:11:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just figured it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.56,0:11:50.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know who killed Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.56,0:11:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you talking about, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.50,0:11:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer's obviously that bandaged guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:11:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He's probably in the forest right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.17,0:12:01.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,just waiting to get us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.38,0:12:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you really think there's such a person in the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.58,0:12:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think back to the state of Ran's room\Nwhen she was attacked...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.62,0:12:15.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He broke in through the balcony, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.39,0:12:19.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He jumped onto the upstairs balcony from a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.99,0:12:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why were there no mud tracks in Ran's room?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.86,0:12:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was raining outside when the bandaged man snuck in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.14,0:12:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.20,0:12:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.01,0:12:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because the bandaged man was inside the lodge!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.54,0:12:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The point of entry was most likely Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room, right next to Ran's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.54,0:12:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Ran & Conan"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.01,0:12:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Chikako"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.81,0:12:44.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer exited onto the balcony, entered Ran's room, and attacked her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.75,0:12:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then she screamed...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.16,0:12:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and he hastily ran back to Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.69,0:12:58.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He quickly changed his clothes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.03,0:13:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and met everyone in Ran's room with feigned unawareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.97,0:13:07.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the maniac who killed Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and attacked Ran
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.98,0:13:11.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is in this very room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.11,0:13:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}. Playing detective is nice and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.05,0:13:15.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but think clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.85,0:13:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the bandaged dude ran past the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.99,0:13:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,every one of us was inside the lodge!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.06,0:13:27.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None of us could possibly be him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.93,0:13:31.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you used a dummy and some piano wire,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.60,0:13:35.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it'd be possible to make it seem that way from inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.00,0:13:36.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dummy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.40,0:13:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. An inflatable one, most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.04,0:13:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He affixed Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body to the dummy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.51,0:13:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and attached two piano wires to the dummy's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.48,0:13:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He passed one wire through the central balcony's railing,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.22,0:13:58.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tied both ends of the wires to the railing above the window in question,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.53,0:14:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then cut the wire that went through the railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.53,0:14:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he swung it past the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.27,0:14:12.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he quickly recovered\Nthe dummy and Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.61,0:14:14.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Chikako!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.84,0:14:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one who could've pulled that off
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.54,0:14:20.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was the person on the balcony, fixing the roof...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.81,0:14:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...you, Takahashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.59,0:14:27.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're kidding, right, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.39,0:14:32.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The two distinct piano wire marks on the outside railing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.76,0:14:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,are proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.60,0:14:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only the stage manager for your old filmmaking club
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.00,0:14:42.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,could've set up something so elaborate!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.91,0:14:49.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what did I do with the body after I pulled it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.81,0:14:54.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right after that, we all chased him into the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.01,0:14:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,where we found Chikako's body in pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.49,0:15:01.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see me carrying any bodies?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.65,0:15:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.56,0:15:06.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is proof that you carried her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.53,0:15:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister found Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s choker by the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.36,0:15:14.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was wearing that choker when she was abducted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.03,0:15:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that it was by the front door after everyone left
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.70,0:15:23.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,means that someone went through the door, carrying her body!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.04,0:15:26.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already told you, I wasn't carrying anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.88,0:15:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, nobody could carry the body without being noticed...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.32,0:15:33.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Assuming it was the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.29,0:15:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it were just the head...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.39,0:15:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...it would be entirely possible to carry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.33,0:15:39.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.69,0:15:43.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, all that we saw outside the window
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was her head surrounded by a cape!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.13,0:15:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her body had been torn apart when we found it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.24,0:15:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.37,0:15:57.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would I want to kill her and Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.01,0:16:01.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And besides—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.25,0:16:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And besides what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.22,0:16:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why won't you say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.92,0:16:09.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't there proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.36,0:16:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You and the bandaged man have completely different figures...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.26,0:16:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Takahashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.70,0:16:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bandaged man isn't fat!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.03,0:16:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takahashi! Why didn't you say so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.84,0:16:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was afraid of what I would ask in response:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.81,0:16:31.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Are you really, truly fat?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.48,0:16:36.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. He's not fat at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.72,0:16:40.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stuffed the head in his shirt and carried it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.39,0:16:44.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, he lured Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Ninto the forest, ripped her apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.89,0:16:48.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,replaced the padding under his shirt with her head,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.46,0:16:50.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and carried it back to the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.50,0:16:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, after doing the trick on the balcony,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.00,0:16:57.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he stuffed the deflated dummy and head under his shirt
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.47,0:17:00.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and headed for the forest with everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.17,0:17:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he dumped the head in the forest
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.41,0:17:05.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,while pretending to look for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.01,0:17:09.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, this was a daring and clever trick
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.25,0:17:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in which he faked his figure to freely move the corpse around!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.16,0:17:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By using this trick, he was able to make it look like
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.69,0:17:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the bandaged man took Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} into the forest and killed her,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.70,0:17:30.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and that he was responsible for everything that happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.30,0:17:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But his supposedly-perfect plan
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.87,0:17:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,began to mess up when Ran did something...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.98,0:17:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. When she accidentally opened his door,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.78,0:17:43.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she saw it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.32,0:17:49.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...his real figure!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.42,0:17:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She hadn't thought much of it at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.39,0:17:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but if she did remember,\Nhis carefully-planned murder plot
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.53,0:18:00.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,would go up in smoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.07,0:18:03.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he attacked her in the forest—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.20,0:18:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to keep her quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.94,0:18:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.68,0:18:12.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Worried that Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would go down the mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:14.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,during all the commotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.88,0:18:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he cut the phone line, destroyed the bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.69,0:18:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and shut everyone up inside the lodge!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.56,0:18:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He lured Chikako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} into the forest as planned
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.33,0:18:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then murdered her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.60,0:18:30.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was lured out by the note
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.46,0:18:34.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that he most likely slipped under her door.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.97,0:18:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably about fellow club member Atsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.64,0:18:42.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who committed suicide two years ago—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.51,0:18:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true! I did it all for Atsuko!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.48,0:18:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takahashi...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.32,0:18:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She secretly showed me a story she had written,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.12,0:18:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and her eyes sparkled as she told me\Nher dream of being a novelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.89,0:19:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, one day, she hanged herself in our meeting room!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.69,0:19:04.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once I saw Chikako's latest movie,\N"Blue Kingdom",
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.40,0:19:07.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suddenly knew why she did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.87,0:19:09.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Blue Kingdom"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.73,0:19:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me she—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.34,0:19:14.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. The story for Chikako's debut work
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.21,0:19:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was exactly the same as the "Azure Country"\Nstory that Atsuko showed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.58,0:19:21.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean Chikako...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.81,0:19:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...stole it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.05,0:19:26.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The story won Chikako a new scriptwriter's award
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.49,0:19:32.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,while she was still in school, and now she's famous!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.03,0:19:34.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how do we know that led to Atsuko's suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.49,0:19:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The day Chikako won the award—\Nthe day before Atsuko died—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.83,0:19:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Atsuko told me over the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.30,0:19:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that she couldn't trust anyone anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.64,0:19:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I lured Chikako into the forest\Nwith a blackmail note
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.14,0:19:52.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then I chopped her head off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.18,0:19:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what she gets for crushing Atsuko's dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.05,0:20:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all over now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.99,0:20:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's time for me to see Atsuko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.79,0:20:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Takahashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.20,0:20:06.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stay away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.33,0:20:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takahashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.53,0:20:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to live with her in the next world
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.33,0:20:12.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as the messenger of justice who avenged her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.47,0:20:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop fooling yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.74,0:20:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wanna die, then die!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.57,0:20:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.67,0:20:25.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe you did commit a crime for Atsuko's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.88,0:20:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when you attacked Ran,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.68,0:20:30.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it wasn't for her sake at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.62,0:20:32.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were afraid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.09,0:20:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were afraid of being labeled a criminal, so you attacked her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.82,0:20:39.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're no...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.19,0:20:41.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...messenger of justice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.43,0:20:44.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're just an ugly, bloodthirsty killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.45,0:21:02.38,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A friend's betrayal led to a friend's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.38,0:21:06.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}which, in turn, twisted a friend's heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.39,0:21:12.03,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}At long last, the villa breaks free of the cold and tragic night...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.03,0:21:13.89,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But beware!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.89,0:21:16.50,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Let your guard down, and he'll appear
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.50,0:21:19.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}from a person's heart again...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.60,0:21:23.33,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The crazed killer known as "revenge."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.80,0:22:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad your sister is doing better now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.07,0:23:00.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.70,0:23:04.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She stayed in bed for a whole week after it happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.44,0:23:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was all thanks to your great detective skills
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.74,0:23:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that the case was solved!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.84,0:23:12.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.05,0:23:13.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Uh oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.65,0:23:17.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You make a pretty cool detective, you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.12,0:23:18.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I better change the topic!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.65,0:23:19.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, guess what—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.82,0:23:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, cases like that are as easy as pie for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.66,0:23:28.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and your dad are out of luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.23,0:23:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the great detective Suzuki Sonoko's time now!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.57,0:23:41.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Having her be the detective was definitely a big mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.11,0:23:49.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Dr. Yoko has a motive for killing Nakamoto{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.62,0:23:53.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But she has an airtight alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.15,0:23:55.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If she was the killer, then-
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.76,0:23:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no VCR here...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.23,0:24:03.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Aha! So that's how!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.00,0:24:08.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This was an alibi trick involving Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-chan{\r\be10}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.28,0:24:15.20,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.20,0:24:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Curtains
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.00,0:24:22.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time even the subtitle is unique!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.99,0:24:24.62,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
